## Running

```bash
go mod tidy
go run .
```

## Development

`just dev` watches Go, template, and config files and rebuilds +
restarts the server on change{{ if .HasFrontend }}. It also runs
the frontend asset watcher in parallel (tailwind CLI in JS mode,
vite in TS mode). Refresh the browser to see changes{{ end }}.

Install the watcher once:

```bash
go install github.com/air-verse/air@latest
```

Then:

```bash
just dev              # watch mode (Ctrl+C to stop)
just run              # one-shot, no watching
just build            # produce bin/{{.BinaryName}}
{{- if .HasFrontend }}
just build-fe         # produce public/{css,js}/*
just build-all        # both binary + frontend
{{- end }}
```

## Configuration

Config is layered from three kinds of sources, in order:

1. **Framework defaults** — each enabled hex provider ships its own TOML
   + CUE schema (see `app/provider/config.go` for the Sources list).
   These live inside the framework module; they're never copied into
   your repo automatically at runtime.
2. **Your `config/` directory** — files under `config/*.toml` override
   framework defaults per-field. `hex init` publishes a starter copy
   for every component you enabled, so you can inspect and edit them
   right away.
3. **Environment variables** — bind config keys to env vars via
   `config/env.yaml` (not scaffolded by default). `.env` loading is
   opt-in in `app/provider/config.go`.

### Validation with CUE

`config/schema.cue` is where you add validation constraints for your
own application-specific config namespaces. Framework namespaces
(`database`, `server`, `log`, `cache`, `telemetry`) already have
schemas that ship inside each provider — you don't need to redeclare
their shapes.

## Publishing framework configs

Every enabled hex component published its default config at
`hex init` time. To opt into a component you didn't enable initially,
or to refresh a copy after upgrading hex:

```bash
hex publish cache           # copy hex/cache/provider config into config/
hex publish web             # copy hex/web/provider config into config/
hex publish --all           # publish every framework component
hex publish log --force     # overwrite an existing local copy
```

Available components: `cache`, `db`, `log`, `telemetry`, `web`.

If you also want to *wire* a new component into `app/boot.go`, edit
`app/provider/config.go` to add the provider's `Configs()` to the
Sources list, then register the provider in `app/boot.go`. See
`app/provider/log.go` for the pattern.

## Generators

Add code with the `hex` CLI (from the project root):

```bash
hex make:provider payments        # app/provider/payments.go, wired into app/boot.go
hex make:domain user              # domain/user/{user,repository,service,errors}.go
hex make:migration create_users   # database/migrations/<ts>_create_users.{up,down}.sql
hex make:command hello            # app/command/hello.go, wired into root cobra tree
hex make:adapter cache/redis      # infrastructure/cache/redis/redis.go stub
```

## Build

